text: Neadmete unalashkensis is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cancellariidae, the nutmeg snails. ==Description== The shell grows to a length of 18 mm. ==Distribution== This species occurs in the Pacific Ocean from Alaska to Oregon, USA ==References== * Turgeon, D.
